    {
      "id": "project-four",
      "label": "Project 04",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "uid": "basxgkz1c",
          "type": "eyebrow-heading",
          "eyebrow": "",
          "headline": "Year in Review"
        },
        {
          "uid": "b3kb2de9c",
          "type": "meta"
        },
        {
          "uid": "bo2yxzp7n",
          "type": "section-label",
          "label": "Overview"
        },
        {
          "uid": "bpyzdxl16",
          "type": "text",
          "body": "At the end of every year, we gave users a reason to look back. PayZapp Wrapped was a personalised, interactive flipbook experience — swipeable cards revealing key insights from a user's year on the app. Top spend categories, biggest transactions, most used features. Pure delight, no utility agenda."
        },
        {
          "uid": "bc26dpcfz",
          "type": "spacer",
          "size": "md"
        },
        {
          "uid": "b70e9b1qa",
          "type": "section-label",
          "label": "why"
        },
        {
          "uid": "bmfrbbja4",
          "type": "text",
          "body": "Payments are functional by nature. Year Wrapped was our one moment to make the app feel personal. If a user sees their own story reflected back at them, the app stops being a tool and starts being something they have a relationship with."
        },
